  <h5>African Art</h5>
  <hr />
  <p>Art of Africa constitutes one of the most diverse creations, owing to the large amounts of independent societies and civilizations, each with its own artistic culture.  African art also includes art by African Disporas, such as African Americans.  Characteristics common to most art from African culture include: emphasis on human forms, visual abstraction (as opposed to naturalistic representation), sculpture emphasis, three-dimensional qualities, and nonlinear scaling.</p></div>
